DATA PROTECTION POLICY
================================================================================
Company: Ahmnest SecureTech Solution
Effective Date: [Date]
Version: 1.0
================================================================================

1. PURPOSE
================================================================================
This policy establishes requirements for protecting sensitive data including
customer PII, financial records, and intellectual property in compliance with
Nigerian Data Protection Regulation (NDPR).

2. DATA CLASSIFICATION
================================================================================
| Classification | Definition | Examples |
|----------------|------------|----------|
| Public | Freely shareable | Marketing materials, contact info |
| Internal | Company-wide access | Policies, procedures, org charts |
| Confidential | Restricted access | Financial records, HR data |
| Highly Confidential | Severely restricted | Customer PII, trade secrets, IP |

3. DATA PROTECTION CONTROLS
================================================================================
| Control | Public | Internal | Confidential | Highly Confidential |
|---------|--------|----------|--------------|---------------------|
| Encryption (at rest) | Not Required | Recommended | Required | Required |
| Encryption (in transit) | Recommended | Required | Required | Required |
| Access Control | Open | Role-Based | Need-to-Know | Strictly Need-to-Know |
| MFA | Not Required | Recommended | Required | Required |
| Audit Logging | Not Required | Recommended | Required | Required |
| Data Retention | 1 Year | 3 Years | 5 Years | 7 Years |

4. DATA LIFECYCLE MANAGEMENT
================================================================================
| Stage | Requirements | Owner |
|-------|---------------|-------|
| Creation | Classification, encryption | Data Creator |
| Storage | Access controls, backups | IT/Data Owner |
| Usage | Need-to-know, logging | Authorized Users |
| Sharing | Secure channels, approval | Data Owner |
| Archiving | Encryption, access control | IT/Compliance |
| Destruction | Secure deletion, certification | IT/Compliance |

5. BREACH NOTIFICATION (NDPR Compliance)
================================================================================
| Type | Timeframe | Method |
|------|-----------|--------|
| Internal | 1 Hour | Emergency Notification |
| Management | 4 Hours | Incident Report |
| Legal Counsel | 8 Hours | Formal Notification |
| NITDA | 72 Hours | Official Filing |
| Affected Clients | 48 Hours | Formal Letter |

6. DATA SHARING GUIDELINES
================================================================================
- Internal sharing: Only on need-to-know basis
- External sharing: Requires approval and secure channel
- Cloud services: Approved services only
- Mobile devices: Company-approved devices only

================================================================================
